*devtray-0.4.1-r1 (14 Sep 2008)

  14 Sep 2008; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org> +devtray-0.4.1-r1.ebuild:
  With the advent of split gnome-python-desktop, we only need the libwnck
  portion, not the whole ugly mess of gnome apps. So remove the gnome USE
  flag and always use libwnck.

  30 Aug 2008; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org> devtray-0.4.1.ebuild:
  x86 stable, bug #236057

  28 Aug 2008; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org> -devtray-0.3.3.ebuild,
  devtray-0.4.1.ebuild:
  Marking stable on amd64

*devtray-0.4.1 (11 May 2008)

  11 May 2008; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org>
  -files/DevTray-0.3.2-no_pycups.patch, -devtray-0.3.2-r1.ebuild,
  devtray-0.3.3.ebuild, +devtray-0.4.1.ebuild:
  New version 0.4.1 was released

*devtray-0.3.3 (22 Jan 2008)

  22 Jan 2008; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org> +devtray-0.3.3.ebuild:
  Version bump (Bug #207055)

  29 Nov 2007; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org> -devtray-0.3.2.ebuild:
  Version cleanup

*devtray-0.3.2-r1 (28 Nov 2007)

  28 Nov 2007; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org> +devtray-0.3.2-r1.ebuild:
  Added pyalsaaudio and cddb-py optional dependencies

*devtray-0.3.2 (26 Nov 2007)

  26 Nov 2007; Jim Ramsay <lack@gentoo.org>
  +files/DevTray-0.3.2-no_pycups.patch, +metadata.xml,
  +devtray-0.3.2.ebuild:
  New package: DevTray is a rox panel applet which shows HAL devices.

